        <p>The very end of the harbor wall is where one of the seven wonders of the ancient world was though to have stood, the Colossus of Rhodes. This massive bronze statue stood over 100 feet tall (30 m) at the entrance to the ancient port of Rhodes over 2,200 years ago.</p>
