        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Lindos, Greece</h2>
        <p>In the town of Lindos you'll find the awe-inspiring <strong>Lindos Acropolis</strong>, an ancient hilltop citadel used by many different cultures over thousands of years including the Greeks, Romans, and Byzantines. This giant fortification sits atop a hill high above the coast, surrounded by beautiful white houses and buildings.</p>
        <p>Within the Acropolis you'll find many ancient and medieval structures, the most impressive being the partially-standing ancient Greek columned structures. From atop you can also take in breathtaking panoramic views over the extremely scenic landscape and coastline around Lindos.</p>
        <p>Be sure to see the sandy <strong>Lindos Beach</strong> with its clear green waters and incredible views of the Acropolis. On the other side of the Acropolis is the gorgeous <strong>St. Paul's Bay</strong>, which has two tiny beaches and is also very scenic, hosting views of the backside of the Acropolis.</p>
